docs.snippet: It is important for Americans reading about Soviet trade deals with Latin-American countries to keep their perspective. Late last year there was agreement on a three-year, $100-million accord between Brazil and the Soviet Union, whose details are now...
docs.lead_paragraph: It is important for Americans reading about Soviet trade deals with Latin-American countries to keep their perspective. Late last year there was agreement on a three-year, $100-million accord between Brazil and the Soviet Union, whose details are now being worked out. Last February the Soviet Union agreed to buy sugar these next five years from Cuba, and still earlier Argentina had made an even larger deal on paper.
